      "content": "Here's the revised draft:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out and thank you for taking the time to interview for our Senior Developer role at [Company Name]. Our team was impressed by your technical skills and experience, and we were pleased to learn more about your approach to [specific topic or area of expertise]. Although we ultimately decided to move forward with another candidate whose background aligned more closely with our specific cloud architecture needs, we want to assure you that this decision was in no way a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer. As always, our hiring decisions are never easy, especially when talented candidates like you are part of the process, and we appreciate the challenges this role brings.\n\nWe were truly impressed by your fit and expertise, and we'd love to keep your resume on file for future openings that may be a better match for your talents. We believe that your skills would be a great asset to our team at some point in the future, and we'd be happy to reach out if another opportunity arises.\n\nBest regards, [Your Name]\n\nThis revised version adds a bit more warmth and personality, while still being professional and honest. The phrase \"we'd love to keep your resume on file for future openings\" feels more personal",
